{title: Fly Trouble}
{artist: Hank Williams}
{composer: Written by Fred Rose, Bunny Biggs, Honey Wilds}

[C]Did you ever sit straight up in bed
With [F]somethin' a circlin' round your head
And you [C]swat at it as it whizzes by
And it's [G7]just one pesky little [C]fly

You shake your head and twitch your nose
And [F]settle down in sweet repose
And [C]when you're just about to doze  [G7]fly [C]trouble
[F]Buzz buzz buzz goes that [C]busy little fly
[D7]Buzz buzz buzz he's [G7]takin' off to hide
You [C]roll a paper up nice and tight
And [F]wait around for him to light
But [C]there's a fly that's a livin' right
[G7]Buzz buzz [C]buzz
Now the toughest hide grows on a mule
Cause [F]he's a bulky stubborn fool
He [C]likes to look at you and glare
And [G7]never even move a [C]hair

But when his muscles start to twitch
And [F]when his tail begins to swish
That [C]mule ain't bothered with an itch  [G7]fly [C]trouble
[F]Buzz buzz buzz goes that [C]busy little pest
[D7]Buzz buzz buzz that mule [G7]can't get no rest
He [C]shakes his head and bats his eye
And [F]kicks his heels up to the sky
Did [C]you ever see a jackass cry
[G7]Buzz buzz [C]buzz

Now you pick a perfect night in June
With [F]flowers a bloomin' neath the moon
And [C]your light of love is burnin' bright
And you [G7]tell yourself tonight's the night
You [C]brace yourself and your courage grows
An on [F]your knees where you'll propose
When [C]somethin' bites you on the nose  [G7]fly [C]trouble
[F]Buzz buzz buzz goes that [C]busy little thing
[D7]Buzz buzz buzz you [G7]swat and lose the ring
You [C]fan the air as he goes by
and [F]stick your finger in your eye
Hit [C]everything except that fly
[G7]Buzz buzz [C]buzz